Why NL Eats?
Sustainable Agriculture

Our hydroponic units use 90% less water than traditional soil farming, making them sustainable and ideal for indoor use, reducing transportation and carbon emissions.

STEM Learning

Hydroponics transforms classrooms into living labs, providing students with hands-on STEM learning experiences in sustainable agriculture.

Healthy Eating

The locally-grown produce from our hydroponic units encourages healthy eating, benefiting the school cafeteria with nutritious options for students and staff, with surplus available for local food banks.

Skill Development

Engaging with our hydroponic units cultivates vital skills such as teamwork, problem-solving, and critical thinking in students, boosting both their academic achievement and future career readiness.

Our Mission

Empowering the next generation through sustainable hydroponic gardening for hands-on STEM learning and positive community impact.

Our Vision

Our vision is for all schools to utilize hydroponic technology, offering fresh, locally-grown food to students and staff, while nurturing future sustainability leaders.

Our Goals

Integrate hydroponics into high school curriculums nationwide to enhance STEM learning with hands-on experience and make fresh, local produce more accessible in communities.

Our Impact

Since our start, we've provided modular hydroponic units to many schools, benefiting thousands of students. Our initiative has turned classrooms into green spaces and increased community access to fresh, nutritious food.
